<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang=en>
	<head>
		<!-- Required meta tags -->
	    <meta charset="utf-8">
	    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, shrink-to-fit=no">

	    <!-- Bootstrap CSS -->
	    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.1.3/css/bootstrap.min.css" integrity="sha384-MCw98/SFnGE8fJT3GXwEOngsV7Zt27NXFoaoApmYm81iuXoPkFOJwJ8ERdknLPMO" crossorigin="anonymous">

	    <!-- own styling -->
	    <link rel="stylesheet" href="../styles/base.css">
		<title>Staty by JotForm</title>
	</head>

	<body>
		
		<% include partials/nav.ejs %>

		<div class="container col-11">
			<div class="row">
			    <div class="col-sm-3">
			    	<h1 id="header">Staty</h1>
					<p id="note">by JotForm</p>
			    </div>
			    <div class="col-sm-8">
			      	<p id="intro">Staty is a statistic viewer application for your payment forms on JotForm. You can see your earnings from each form on <a href="/myforms">my forms</a> page. Click on a form's name to see detailed statistics of each form individually.</p> 
			      	<p> Staty is an internship project for JotForm. For details, please visit the <a href="https://github.com/unauo/staty">GitHub page</a> of this project.
			      	<p><a href="/myforms">I am curious already, take me to my forms!</a></p>
			    </div>
			</div>
			<br>
			<div class="container col-11">
				<h3> But... what does Staty really do? What are some features? </h3>
				<br>
				<p> Staty is a third-party app developed using <a href="https://api.jotform.com/docs/">JotForm API</a>, JavaScript and some other stuff. When you authenticate Staty, it looks for all your payment forms, creates detailed tables and graphs to show you the overall statistics of your forms, as well as individual form statistics. You can see how much a form of yours earned you over time, which product of yours was sold more, or how much donation you got over the past weeks. </p>
				<p> Staty shows you the statistics of your forms regardless of them being enabled or disabled forms. Hence you can see your old sales' statistics. You can also sort all tables with respect to any field you want using the little triangle on the left of each field. The default sorting is by <i>name</i> for the forms and <i>total paid</i> for the submissions.</p>
			</div> 
		</div>
		
		<!-- JotForm -->
		<script src="https://js.jotform.com/JotForm.js"></script>
	    <!-- jQuery first, then Popper.js, then Bootstrap JS -->
	    <script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.3.1.slim.min.js" integrity="sha384-q8i/X+965DzO0rT7abK41JStQIAqVgRVzpbzo5smXKp4YfRvH+8abtTE1Pi6jizo" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
	    <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/popper.js/1.14.3/umd/popper.min.js" integrity="sha384-ZMP7rVo3mIykV+2+9J3UJ46jBk0WLaUAdn689aCwoqbBJiSnjAK/l8WvCWPIPm49" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
	    <script src="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.1.3/js/bootstrap.min.js" integrity="sha384-ChfqqxuZUCnJSK3+MXmPNIyE6ZbWh2IMqE241rYiqJxyMiZ6OW/JmZQ5stwEULTy" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
		<script>
			// JotForm authentication
			window.addEventListener("load", function(){
				var apiKey;
				if (window.localStorage.getItem("apiKey")) {
					var apiKey = window.localStorage.getItem("apiKey");
				}
				else {
					JF.login(
				    	function success(){
				    		var apiKey = JF.getAPIKey();
			 	        	window.localStorage.setItem("apiKey", apiKey);
			 			},
				        function error(err){
				        	console.log(err);
							window.alert("oops something went wrong.");
						}
			    	);
				}
			});
		</script>
		
	</body>
</html>

